{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Motivation: Global vs. Local Statistics"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Word2Vec learns from local context windows, seeing one window at a time. It never explicitly uses global corpus statistics — how often word "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "italic"
              }
            ],
            "text": "i"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " appears anywhere near word "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "italic"
              }
            ],
            "text": "j"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " across the entire corpus. GloVe (Global Vectors for Word Representation, Pennington et al., 2014) builds a co-occurrence matrix first and then learns vectors that approximate the log of those counts. The result is faster convergence and, on analogy benchmarks, better accuracy than Word2Vec trained for equivalent time."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "GloVe pipeline: Step 1 shows a co-occurrence matrix where 'ice' co-occurs frequently with 'water' and 'solid' but rarely with 'gas'; Step 2 shows the GloVe loss objective; the result is a vector space where ice/snow cluster separately from steam/gas, and analogy arithmetic like king−man+woman≈queen works."
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The GloVe Objective"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Let "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "X_ij"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " be the number of times word "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "italic"
              }
            ],
            "text": "j"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " appears in the context of word "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "italic"
              }
            ],
            "text": "i"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". GloVe minimises a weighted least-squares loss that pushes the dot product of the two word vectors to equal the log co-occurrence count:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockMath",
        "attrs": {
          "latex": "J = \\sum_{i,j=1}^{V} f(X_{ij}) \\left( \\mathbf{w}_i^\\top \\tilde{\\mathbf{w}}_j + b_i + \\tilde{b}_j - \\log X_{ij} \\right)^2"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "w_i"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — word vector for word "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "italic"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "i"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "w̃_j"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — separate context vector for word "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "italic"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "j"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " (summed with "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "w_i"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " at inference)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "b_i, b̃_j"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — scalar bias terms"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "f(X_ij)"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — weighting function that caps the influence of very frequent pairs so they don't dominate training"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The weighting function is defined as:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockMath",
        "attrs": {
          "latex": "f(x) = \\begin{cases} (x / x_{\\max})^\\alpha & \\text{if } x < x_{\\max} \\\\ 1 & \\text{otherwise} \\end{cases}"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The authors use "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "x_max = 100"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "α = 0.75"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". Pairs rarer than 100 get downweighted; the 0.75 exponent softens the penalty for rare pairs (same trick used in Word2Vec negative sampling)."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Using Pretrained GloVe Vectors"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Stanford distributes pretrained GloVe vectors trained on Wikipedia + Gigaword (6B tokens) and Common Crawl (840B tokens). For most tasks the 6B 300d model is a good starting point."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import numpy as np\n\ndef load_glove(path):\n    \"\"\"Load a GloVe .txt file into a word→vector dict.\"\"\"\n    vectors = {}\n    with open(path, encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n        for line in f:\n            parts = line.split()\n            word = parts[0]\n            vectors[word] = np.array(parts[1:], dtype=np.float32)\n    return vectors\n\n# Download from https://nlp.stanford.edu/projects/glove/\n# e.g. glove.6B.zip → glove.6B.300d.txt\nwv = load_glove(\"glove.6B.300d.txt\")\nprint(wv[\"king\"].shape)   # (300,)\n\ndef cosine(a, b):\n    return np.dot(a, b) / (np.linalg.norm(a) * np.linalg.norm(b))\n\nprint(cosine(wv[\"cat\"], wv[\"dog\"]))    # ~0.92\nprint(cosine(wv[\"cat\"], wv[\"table\"]))  # ~0.57"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Via Gensim"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import gensim.downloader as api\n\n# Downloads ~822 MB; cached after first run\nwv = api.load(\"glove-wiki-gigaword-300\")\n\nprint(wv.most_similar(\"python\", topn=5))\n# [('perl', 0.80), ('ruby', 0.78), ('php', 0.76), ...]\n\n# Classic analogy: king - man + woman\nresult = wv.most_similar(positive=[\"king\", \"woman\"], negative=[\"man\"], topn=1)\nprint(result)   # [('queen', 0.85)]"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "GloVe as Embedding Layer in a Neural Network"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A common pattern is to initialise an "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "nn.Embedding"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " layer with pretrained GloVe weights and fine-tune during training:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import torch\nimport torch.nn as nn\nimport gensim.downloader as api\nimport numpy as np\n\nwv = api.load(\"glove-wiki-gigaword-100\")   # 100-dim, smaller download\nvocab = list(wv.key_to_index.keys())       # ~400k words\n\n# Build embedding matrix: row i = vector for word i\nembedding_matrix = np.zeros((len(vocab), 100), dtype=np.float32)\nfor i, word in enumerate(vocab):\n    embedding_matrix[i] = wv[word]\n\n# Create an nn.Embedding and load the pretrained weights\nembedding = nn.Embedding(len(vocab), 100)\nembedding.weight = nn.Parameter(torch.from_numpy(embedding_matrix))\n\n# Optionally freeze to prevent fine-tuning:\n# embedding.weight.requires_grad = False\n\nword_to_idx = {w: i for i, w in enumerate(vocab)}\n\ntokens = [\"the\", \"cat\", \"sat\"]\nidxs   = torch.tensor([word_to_idx[t] for t in tokens])\nvecs   = embedding(idxs)   # shape (3, 100)\nprint(vecs.shape)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
