      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Shared Limitations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "GloVe and Word2Vec share the same fundamental limitation: one vector per word type with no context sensitivity. \"Bank\" receives a single averaged vector regardless of whether it appears in \"river bank\" or \"bank account.\" This is the problem ELMo and BERT solve by producing context-dependent embeddings."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Polysemy"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": one vector per word-type, not per word-sense."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "OOV words"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": no representation for words absent from training. FastText addresses this with character n-grams."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Corpus bias"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": vectors from Wikipedia reflect encyclopaedic language; vectors from Twitter reflect informal language. Domain matters."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
